diff:1618266697:1618266697:=1,60d0%0a%3c :Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity%0a%3c :Essential: {Category.MorphosyntacticDiversity$:essential}%0a%3c :Title: Null or Zero Copula in African American English%0a%3c :Author: khushiw%0a%3c :Section: B%0a%3c :Completed: 12.04.2021 - 15:31%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c Summary: \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c The grammatical exclusion of "to be" verbs in African American English%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c African American Language (AAL) has a unique grammatical construction that involves the dropping of "to be" verbs. Commonly, this is called Null Copula or Zero Copula. This is apparent in common sentences from AAL/AAVE such as "she runnin'" or "she home yesterday". Although seemingly random, this grammatical construction follows a very clear set of rules:%0a%3c %0a%3c 1. copula cannot be omitted if unstressed%0a%3c 2. copula cannot be omitted at the end of a phrase%0a%3c 3. copula cannot be omitted for first-person subjects%0a%3c 4. copula cannot be omitted when negated%0a%3c 5. copula cannot be omitted in its infinitive form "to be"%0a%3c 6. copula cannot be omitted in the past tense%0a%3c 7. copula cannot be omitted in the AAVE remote present perfect (not in standard English)%0a%3c 8. copula cannot be omitted in a confirmatory tag question%0a%3c %0a%3c The omission of a copula is present in many different languages beyond English. AAL/AAVE is a dialect of English in which it is very prevalent.%0a%3c %0a%3c Sources: https://ygdp.yale.edu/african-american-language-and-grammatical-diversity-2020#grammar-and-systematicity%0a%3c http://www.ling.ohio-state.edu/~nvail/202/SP03/materials/aave.txt%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
